</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32CE29E6C58FF96FF6CCAA4FAFAFB5C" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CCAA4FEB5FB74" blockId="54.[146,770,1190,1474]" box="[146,312,1190,1210]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<figureCitation id="130DAD906C58FF96FF6CCAA4FEB5FB74" box="[146,312,1190,1210]" captionStart="Plate 19" captionStartId="54.[146,187,1014,1031]" captionTargetBox="[165,1442,147,979]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Plate 19. Emargininae. Fig. 249, Thoreauella sp., USNMENT01022106. Fig. 250, Thoreauella sp., USNMENT01525887." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 249 and 250</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CCAC1FE21FA0F" blockId="54.[146,770,1190,1474]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
This unusual group of diminutive wasps has been variously classified, often as eucoilines. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FE68CAE2FDB9FB3A" author="Ronquist, F." box="[406,564,1248,1268]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="139 - 164" refId="ref27728" refString="Ronquist, F. 1999. Phylogeny, classification and evolution of the Cynipoidea. Zool. Scr. 28: 139 - 164." type="journal article" year="1999">Ronquist (1999)</bibRefCitation>
clarified the circumscription of the group and recognized them as their own subfamily (reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FEF3CB19FE36FAE1" author="Pujade-Villar, J." box="[269,443,1307,1327]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="18 - 65" refId="ref26801" refString="Pujade-Villar, J. 2019. Reclasificacion de los grandes taxa de Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera) desde Weld (1952) hasta 2017: la historia de una lucha evolutiva entre el parasitoidismo y la fitofagia. Folia Entomol. Mex. 5: 18 - 65." type="journal article" year="2019">Pujade-Villar 2019</bibRefCitation>
). While typically rare in most parts of the world, they are a dominant figitid group in 
<collectingCountry id="F321F1856C58FF96FD9CCB3AFD5EFA82" box="[610,723,1336,1356]" name="Madagascar" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FD1FCB3BFEBEFAA4" author="van Noort, S. &amp; M. L. Buffington &amp; M. Forshage" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref26147" refString="van Noort, S., M. L. Buffington, and M. Forshage. 2015. Afrotropical Cynipoidea. Zookeys. 493: 1 - 176. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 493.6353." type="journal article" year="2015">van Noort et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Several genera have been described, but all have been synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C36CA966C58FF96FE6FCB71FDDCFA49" authority="Girault" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1930" box="[401,593,1395,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Thoreauella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9426D076C58FF96FE6FCB71FE72FA49" box="[401,511,1395,1415]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoreauella</emphasis>
Girault
</taxonomicName>
; considering that, nothing less than a world-wide revision would be able to find phylogenetically meaningful groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CCBE1FE5BF9DA" blockId="54.[146,770,1507,1556]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Biology. Host unknown, but adults have been collected from formicid refuse piles (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FEA7C802FE44F9DA" author="Weld, L. H." box="[345,457,1536,1556]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref28962" refString="Weld, L. H. 1960 b. A new genus in Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera). Proc. Entomol. Soc. Wash. 62: 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1960">Weld 1960b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CC831FD8BF9AA" blockId="54.[146,770,1587,1636]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Distribution. Pantropical and transgressing into Eastern Palearctic, but rarely collected outside 
<collectingCountry id="F321F1856C58FF96FE6FC852FD8FF9AA" box="[401,514,1616,1636]" name="Madagascar" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CC881FE8BF921" blockId="54.[146,771,1667,1775]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Relevant literature. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FEA4C881FE76F959" author="Ronquist, F." box="[346,507,1667,1687]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="139 - 164" refId="ref27728" refString="Ronquist, F. 1999. Phylogeny, classification and evolution of the Cynipoidea. Zool. Scr. 28: 139 - 164." type="journal article" year="1999">Ronquist (1999)</bibRefCitation>
circumscribed the group; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FF6CC8A2FE9FF97A" author="Weld, L. H." box="[146,274,1696,1716]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref28962" refString="Weld, L. H. 1960 b. A new genus in Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera). Proc. Entomol. Soc. Wash. 62: 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1960">Weld (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
suggested species are ant associates. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA7CCE46C58FF96FD94C8A3FF5DF91C" author="van Noort, S. &amp; M. L. Buffington &amp; M. Forshage" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref26147" refString="van Noort, S., M. L. Buffington, and M. Forshage. 2015. Afrotropical Cynipoidea. Zookeys. 493: 1 - 176. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 493.6353." type="journal article" year="2015">Van Noort et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the Afrotropical species and moved all species into 
<taxonomicName id="4C36CA966C58FF96FF6CC8D9FE8DF921" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1930" box="[146,256,1755,1775]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Thoreauella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9426D076C58FF96FF6CC8D9FE8DF921" box="[146,256,1755,1775]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoreauella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF6CC912FE99F8EA" blockId="54.[146,276,1808,1828]" box="[146,276,1808,1828]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Classification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FF4AC942FE3CF89A" blockId="54.[180,433,1856,1876]" box="[180,433,1856,1876]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="4C36CA966C58FF96FF4AC942FE3CF89A" authority="Kovalev, 1994" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1994" box="[180,433,1856,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Emargininae">Emargininae Kovalev, 1994</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B89B1156C58FF96FC9CCA7CFAFAFB5C" blockId="54.[866,1399,1150,1170]" box="[866,1399,1150,1170]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="4C36CA966C58FF96FC9CCA7CFBD8FB5C" authority="Girault, 1930" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1930" box="[866,1109,1150,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Thoreauella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9426D076C58FF96FC9CCA7CFC5DFB5C" box="[866,976,1150,1170]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoreauella</emphasis>
Girault, 1930
</taxonomicName>
; 15 species pantropical ePAePA
</paragraph>
